'''Peter Gentsch''' (born 24 May 1968) is a German [[management consultant]] and serial [[entrepreneur]] specialising in digital management and [[data science]].<ref>[http://www.briansolis.com/tag/dr-peter-gentsch/ Brian Solis, Tag: Dr. Peter Gentsch], read May 24th, 2017</ref><ref>[https://www.linkedin.com/in/petergentsch/ LinkedIn Profile Peter Gentsch], read May 24, 2017</ref><ref>[https://www.crunchbase.com/person/prof-dr-peter-gentsch#/entity/ Crunchbase: Prof. Dr. Peter Gentsch], read May 24th, 2017</ref>

== Career ==
After his doctorate at the [[WHU-Otto Beisheim School of Management]] (WHU), Peter Gentsch was from 2002–2004 Professor at the [[Technical University of Cologne]] (TH Cologne). Since 2004 Peter Gentsch has held the professorship for International [[Business Administration]] with a focus on digital management and [[data science]] at the Technical and Economic University of Applied Sciences (HTW) in Aalen.<ref>[https://www.hs-aalen.de/de/users/202 University of Applied Sciences Aalen Profile Prof. Dr. rer. pol. Peter Gentsch], German website, read May 24th, 2017</ref> In addition, he works as a [[docent]] and [[reviewer]] at the [[University of St. Gallen]] and at the [[WHU-Otto Beisheim School of Management]]. Gentsch is the author of several publications,<ref>[https://www.hs-aalen.de/en/users/202/seiten/veroffentlichungen Overview of publications, Peter Gentsch], German website, read May 24, 2017</ref> and a seminar and keynote speaker on the subjects of [[Customer relationship management|CRM]], [[social media]],<ref>[https://www.slideshare.net/smics2011/peter-gentsch-how-to-implement-a-social-media-strategy/ How to implement a social media strategy by Peter Gentsch], read May 24, 2017</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fx-xist-008/ Speech: Social Media – More that just another channel! by Peter Gentsch], YouTube Video, seen May 24, 2017</ref> [[business intelligence]], [[digital transformation]] and [[innovation management]].

== Entrepreneurial Activities ==
In 2002, Peter Gentsch founded B.I.G. – Business Intelligence Group in [[Berlin]]<ref>[http://www.competence-site.de/business-intelligence-group-gmbh/ Company Profile Intelligence Group GmbH], German website, read May 24, 2017</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e48h1Jx2ZFc&t=324s/ Speech: Corporate Social Media Management Business Intelligence Group founder Peter Gentsch], YouTube Video, seen May 24, 2017</ref> which now supports various companies (ConversionBoosting, intelliAd, etc.) as a shareholder and investor.<ref>[http://www.silicon.de/41577469/usu-ubernimmt-berliner-b-i-g/ USU takes over B.I.G. in silicon.de, 2012], German website, read May 24, 2017</ref> In 2006 he took over TextTech GmbH, which he developed from a research-oriented organisation into a company established on the market. In 2012 the stock-exchange-registered USU Software AG<ref>[https://www.usu.de/de/ Company profile USU AG], German website, read May 24, 2017</ref> acquired B.I.G. Social Media GmbH,<ref>[http://drakestar.com/news/usu-to-acquire-b-i-g-leading-provider-of-social-media-management-solutions/ USU AG acquires B.I.G. Social Media GmbH], read May 24, 2017</ref><ref>[https://www.usu.de/en/usu-group/companies/big-social-media-gmbh/ Company profile B.I.G. Social Media GmbH], German website, read May 24th, 2017</ref> founded by Peter Gentsch, which continues to operate as an independent unit after the takeover.

Peter Gentsch is also founder and executive board member of DATAlovers AG<ref>[https://www.datalovers.com/company/aufsichtsrat/ Company profile DATAlovers AG], German website, read May 24, 2017</ref> and founder and managing partner of Diva-e Digital Transformation Consulting GmbH.<ref>[http://www.digital-transformation-group.de/ueber-uns/ Company profile Digital Transformation Group], German website, read May 24, 2017</ref><ref>[http://emeram.com/en/press/press-releases/diva-e-digital-value-enterprise-gmbh-strengthens-its-consultancy-expertise/ Emeram Capital Partners GmbH, Press release, October 5, 2017], read May 24, 2017</ref>

In 2000, Peter Gentsch founded the Social Media Excellence-Circle (SME).<ref>[http://www.social-media-excellence.de/uber-uns/initiatoren/ Company Profile Social Media Excellence Circle], German website, read May 24, 2017</ref> This initiative currently has over 400 members from 180 companies. The initiative has set itself the aim of together finding practice-derived solutions for core themes and problems relating to [[Social Media]].

In addition, Peter Gentsch is the co-initiator of the Chief Digital Officer-Club (CDO),<ref>[http://www.digital-transformation-group.de/dtg/pressemitteilung/gruendung-cdo-club-deutschland-fuer-neue-position-des-chief-digital-officers/ Chief Digital Officer-Club], German website, read May 24, 2017</ref> and of the Institute for Customer Experience Management i-CEM. From 2000 to 2008, Peter Gentsch was a member of the jury of the Data Mining Cup.

Peter Gentsch’s main focus is on the planning, conception and realisation of holistic digital, e-business and e-business intelligence concepts. This also includes the use of  [[Big Data]] infrastructures,<ref>[http://www.marketing-on-tour.de/bigdata-die-phantasieluecke-kleiner-machen/ German article: "Big Data: Die Phantasielücke kleiner machen.", in marketing-on-tour.de, 2016], German website, read May 24th, 2017</ref> [[Data Mining]],<ref>[http://www.competence-site.de/data-mining-tools-eine-neue-aera-fuer-das-data-mining/ German article: "Data Mining- Tools – Eine neue Ära für das Data Mining.", in competence-site.de, 2006], German website, read May 24th, 2017</ref> advanced analytics, predictive analytics and Customer Journey management and xIntelligence: multi-channel analytics.<ref>[http://www.digital-transformation-group.de/dtg/interview-mit-prof-dr-peter-gentsch-von-big-data-smart-data-und-social-crm/ German interview with Peter Gentsch], German website, read May 24, 2017</ref> Within these subject fields, Gentsch looks after, among others: [[Audi]], [[BMW]], [[Robert Bosch GmbH|Bosch]], [[Coca-Cola]], [[Daimler AG|Daimler]], [[Deutsche Lufthansa]], [[eBay]], [[ERGO Group]], [[FC Bayern München]], [[Fraport]], [[Google]], [[Microsoft]], [[MLP AG|MLP]], [[Nintendo]], [[Telefónica Germany|O2]], [[Volkswagen]].

== Awards==
* ''German Market Research Innovation Award'': In 2010, Peter Gentsch, together with Lufthansa, won the German Market Research Innovation Award.<ref>[http://bvm.org/fileadmin/images/fotos/PDM/Rueckblick/BVM_inbrief_2-2010_Insight_Mining.pdf German Market Research Innovation Award 2010 in BVN Inbrief August 2010], in German, read May 24, 2017</ref> The study Insight Mining – Modern Data Management Based on Text Mining Technology deals with the efficient handling of the multitude of information sources with which in-house market researchers are confronted on a daily basis.
* ''Digital Communication Award'': In 2011, Gentsch, together with Deutsche Post/DHL, won the international Digital Communication Award in the category “Digital Monitoring and Evaluation”.<ref>[http://www.digital-awards.eu/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/dca_winners_20111.pdf Overview Winner Digital Communication Awards 2011] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161007001546/http://www.digital-awards.eu/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/dca_winners_20111.pdf |date=2016-10-07 }}, in German, read May 24, 2017</ref>
* ''German Award for Online Communication'': In 2014, Peter Gentsch, together with Deutsche Post/DHL, won the German Award for Online Communication in the category “Internal Online Communication”.<ref>[https://www.onlinekommunikationspreis.de/winnerlist2014/ Overview Winner German Online Kommunikationspreis 2014], German website, read May 24, 2017</ref>

